---
layout: layout-base.njk
pagination:
  data: stateSummariesUS
  size: 1
  alias: state
permalink: "/planting-dates/states/{{ state.key }}/index.html"
---

<header class="header">
  <h1>Planting Dates & Crop Timing in {{ state.name }}</h1>

  {% set hero = (state.content and state.content.hero) or {} %}

  {# Optional hero notes (avoid duplicating hero.note if it was used as the lede) #}
  {% if hero %}
    {% set showHeroNote = (hero.note and (not ledeFromHeroNote)) %}
    {% if showHeroNote or hero.extraNote %}
      <div class="callout" style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
        {% if showHeroNote %}
          <p>{{ hero.note }}</p>
        {% endif %}
        {% if hero.extraNote %}
          <p>{{ hero.extraNote }}</p>
        {% endif %}
      </div>
    {% endif %}
  {% endif %}

  {% if state.season and state.season.frost and state.season.frost.spring and state.season.frost.fall %}
  <p>
    In a typical year, the growing season in {{ state.name }} runs roughly from
    <strong>{{ state.season.frost.spring.p50 | mmddLong }}</strong>
    through
    <strong>{{ state.season.frost.fall.p50 | mmddLong }}</strong>.
    {% if state.season.derived and state.season.derived.frostFreeDays_p50 %}
      That’s about <strong>{{ state.season.derived.frostFreeDays_p50 }}</strong> frost-free days for most locations.
    {% endif %}
  </p>
{% endif %}

  {# Lede: prefer explicit hero.lede; otherwise, if hero.note exists, use it as the lede. #}
  {% set ledeFromHeroNote = (hero and hero.note and (not hero.lede)) %}
  {% set lede =
    (hero and hero.lede)
      or (ledeFromHeroNote and hero.note)
      or ("Use this page to get oriented: what a “normal” year usually allows in " + state.name + ", and what tends to be a tight fit. Start with the quick reference, then use the tables for detail.")
  %}
  <p class="lede">{{ lede }}</p>

</header>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Quick Planning Reference</h2>

{# --- Pull base-50 remaining GDD values safely by date (loop-based to avoid repeated-value bugs) --- #}
{% set gddJuly = null %}
{% set gddAug  = null %}
{% set gddSept = null %}

{% for row in (state.gdd_remaining or []) %}
  {% if row.date == "07-01" %}{% set gddJuly = row.gdd %}{% endif %}
  {% if row.date == "08-01" %}{% set gddAug  = row.gdd %}{% endif %}
  {% if row.date == "09-01" %}{% set gddSept = row.gdd %}{% endif %}
{% endfor %}

  <ul>
    {% if state.frost.status == "normal" %}
      <li><strong>Typical first fall frost (median):</strong> {{ state.frost.median50 | mmddLong }}</li>
      <li><strong>Range across the region:</strong> {{ state.frost.earliest50 | mmddLong }} to {{ state.frost.latest50 | mmddLong }}</li>
      <li><strong>Coverage:</strong> {{ state.frost.stationCount }} locations</li>
    {% elif state.frost.status == "frost_free" %}
      <li><strong>Frost:</strong> This region is typically frost-free in the normals dataset.</li>
    {% else %}
      <li><strong>Frost:</strong> Frost normals are not available for this region yet.</li>
    {% endif %}

{% if gddJuly != null %}
  <li><strong>Median GDD remaining on July 1 (base 50):</strong> {{ gddJuly }}</li>
{% endif %}
{% if gddAug != null %}
  <li><strong>Median GDD remaining on August 1 (base 50):</strong> {{ gddAug }}</li>
{% endif %}
{% if gddSept != null %}
  <li><strong>Median GDD remaining on September 1 (base 50):</strong> {{ gddSept }}</li>
{% endif %}

    <li>
      <strong>Best next step:</strong>
      Use the <a href="/tools/growing-degree-day-planner/">Growing Degree Day Planner</a> to check a specific crop and planting date for your exact location.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p class="fine muted" style="margin-top:14px;">
    These values are climate normals (typical conditions), not a forecast. Microclimates can shift real frost timing.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Season Boundaries in {{ state.name }} (Typical Frost Dates)</h2>

  <p class="small" style="margin-top:-0.25rem;">
    This is a climate-normal reference point, not a forecast. A
    <a href="/guides/what-does-50-percent-frost-probability-mean/">“50% probability”</a>
    frost date means that, historically, a <strong>32°F frost</strong> happens by this date in about half of years — and later in about half.
  </p>

  {% if state.frost.status == "normal" %}
    {% set springObj = state.season and state.season.frost and state.season.frost.spring or null %}
    {% set hasSpring = springObj and springObj.p50 and springObj.status == "normal" %}
    {% set hasFFD = state.season and state.season.derived and state.season.derived.frostFreeDays_p50 %}

    <div class="tableWrap">
      <table class="table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            {% if hasSpring %}
              <th>Typical last spring frost (50%)</th>
            {% endif %}
            <th>Typical first fall frost (50%)</th>
            <th>Fall frost range across region</th>
            {% if hasFFD %}
              <th>Typical frost-free days</th>
            {% endif %}
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            {% if hasSpring %}
              <td>{{ springObj.p50 | mmddLong }}</td>
            {% endif %}
            <td>{{ state.frost.median50 | mmddLong }}</td>
            <td>{{ state.frost.earliest50 | mmddLong }} – {{ state.frost.latest50 | mmddLong }}</td>
            {% if hasFFD %}
              <td>{{ state.season.derived.frostFreeDays_p50 }}</td>
            {% endif %}
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p class="small muted" style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
      Based on {{ state.frost.stationCount }} locations in {{ state.name }}.
    </p>

    {% if hasSpring or hasFFD %}
      <p class="small muted" style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
        Use these boundaries as your baseline season window — then lean on crop maturity and remaining heat to judge what will reliably finish in a typical year.
      </p>
    {% endif %}

    <div class="small muted" style="margin-top:.15rem;">
      <p><strong>Why the range matters:</strong> elevation, terrain, and nearby water can shift frost timing a lot within the same region.</p>
      <p><strong><a href="/guides/32f-vs-28f-what-temperature-kills-plants/">Frost vs. hard freeze:</a></strong> 32°F is often a light frost; colder temperatures (often ~28°F) are more likely to cause widespread damage.</p>
    </div>

  {% elif state.frost.status == "frost_free" %}
    <p class="small">
      This region appears to be <strong>typically frost-free</strong> in the normals dataset (no 50% first fall frost date).
    </p>
  {% else %}
    <p class="small">
      Frost normals are not available for this region yet.
    </p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Typical Remaining Growing Degree Days (Base 50)</h2>

    <p class="small" style="margin-top:-0.25rem;">
    <a href="/guides/how-frost-dates-and-growing-degree-days-work-together/">Growing Degree Days</a> (Base 50°F) are a heat-accumulation measure used to estimate plant development.
    “Remaining GDD” is the typical amount of usable heat still available <em>from each date</em> as the season approaches frost risk.
  </p>

    <div class="tableWrap">
    <table class="table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Date</th>
          <th>Base</th>
          <th>Median GDD Remaining</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for row in state.gdd_remaining %}
          <tr>
            <td>{{ row.date | mmddLong }}</td>
            <td>{{ row.base }}</td>
            <td>{% if row.gdd != null %}{{ row.gdd }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
          </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

                  <div class="small muted" style="margin-top:.15rem;">
    <p><strong>How to use it:</strong> compare your crop or variety’s heat requirement to the remaining GDD after your planting date.</p>
    <p><strong>What it helps with:</strong> deciding if a later planting is a reasonable bet, choosing shorter-maturity varieties, and estimating whether a fast crop can still finish.</p>
    <p><strong>Late-season reality:</strong> heat tends to accumulate more slowly as days shorten, so late-season progress can feel slower even when calendar days remain.</p>
  </div>

  {% if state.frost.status != "normal" %}
    <p class="small muted" style="margin-top:-0.25rem;">
      Remaining GDD to “first frost” is not applicable when there is no typical frost date.
    </p>
  {% endif %}

</section>

{% include "region/modules/season-timing-strategy.njk" %}
{% include "region/modules/season-timing.njk" %}
{% include "region/modules/planting-windows.njk" %}
{% include "region/modules/what-can-i-grow.njk" %}

{# Optional one-off details: src/_includes/region/{{ state.key }}-details.njk #}
{% set detailsPath = "region/" + state.key + "-details.njk" %}
{% include detailsPath ignore missing %}

{# Modular region system (regionContent.js drives order) #}
{% if state.content and state.content.modules %}
  {% for mod in state.content.modules %}
    {% include "region/modules/" + mod + ".njk" %}
  {% endfor %}
{% endif %}
